Bujumbura. The Burundian National Media Council (CNC) has warned journalists tarnishing the east African country s image, the CNC vice-chairman said Monday at the celebration of the World Radio Day. Media freedom is real in Burundi. This is a warning against journalists using internet to tarnish Burundi s image, who claim that there s no media freedom here (in Burundi).There are over 33 media companies including more than 24 radio stations, six television stations and three government owned media houses, CNC Vice-Chairman Gabriel Bihumugani told a press conference. According to him, there is good collaboration between the CNC and media in Burundi. (Xinhua)